abstract: Iranian officials and satellite images suggest the Islamic Republic is preparing to a launch a satellite into space after three major failures last year, the latest for a program which the U.S. claims helps Tehran advance its ballistic missile program.
snippet: Iranian officials and satellite images suggest the Islamic Republic is preparing to a launch a satellite into space after three major failures last year, the latest for a program which the U.S. claims helps Tehran advance its ballistic missile pro...
lead_paragraph: DUBAI, United Arab Emirates — Iranian officials and satellite images suggest the Islamic Republic is preparing to a launch a satellite into space after three major failures last year, the latest for a program which the U.S. claims helps Tehran advance its ballistic missile program.
headline_main: Iran, Photos Suggest a US-Criticized Satellite Launch Looms
headline_print_headline: Iran, Photos Suggest a US-Criticized Satellite Launch Looms

abstract: Republicans lack the votes to block witnesses at President Donald Trump's impeachment trial, Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell conceded late Tuesday, a potentially major hurdle for Trump's hopes to end the trial with a quick acquittal. Earlier, Trump's lawyers concluded his defense with a plea to move on.
snippet: Republicans lack the votes to block witnesses at President Donald Trump's impeachment trial, Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell conceded late Tuesday, a potentially major hurdle for Trump's hopes to end the trial with a quick acquittal. Earlie...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Republicans lack the votes to block witnesses at President Donald Trump's impeachment trial, Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell conceded late Tuesday, a potentially major hurdle for Trump's hopes to end the trial with a quick acquittal. Earlier, Trump's lawyers concluded his defense with a plea to move on.
headline_main: GOP Lacks Votes to Block Trial Witnesses, McConnell Concedes
headline_print_headline: GOP Lacks Votes to Block Trial Witnesses, McConnell Concedes

abstract: Corrections that appeared in print on Tuesday, Jan. 28, 2020.
snippet: Corrections that appeared in print on Tuesday, Jan. 28, 2020.
lead_paragraph: An article on Monday about the purchase of newspapers by hedge funds misstated the name of the institution where Ann Marie Lipinski is the curator. It is the Nieman Foundation for Journalism at Harvard University, not the Nieman Center for Journalism.

abstract: John Bolton’s revelations, and the question of whether he would testify, loomed over the Senate trial.
snippet: John Bolton’s revelations, and the question of whether he would testify, loomed over the Senate trial.
lead_paragraph: Read our full story on the day, some key highlights and an analysis of the power Mr. Bolton’s book might have over the president.
headline_main: Impeachment Briefing: Day 2 of Trump’s Defense

abstract: The president’s picked-for-television defense team avoids a ratings “Death Valley,” then gets hit by a Bolton from the blue.
snippet: The president’s picked-for-television defense team avoids a ratings “Death Valley,” then gets hit by a Bolton from the blue.
lead_paragraph: President Trump, reportedly, wanted a telegenic team to make the case for him at his impeachment trial. But the biggest star in the Senate chamber on the first full day of his defense on Monday was The Man Who Wasn’t There.

abstract: Prime Minister Jacinda Ardern may be lauded around the world as a liberal icon but whether she can translate that into a reelection victory in September remains uncertain.
snippet: Prime Minister Jacinda Ardern may be lauded around the world as a liberal icon but whether she can translate that into a reelection victory in September remains uncertain.
lead_paragraph: WELLINGTON, New Zealand — Prime Minister Jacinda Ardern may be lauded around the world as a liberal icon but whether she can translate that into a reelection victory in September remains uncertain.

abstract: Alan Dershowitz argued that demands by United States presidents for specific actions by foreign governments are common.
snippet: Alan Dershowitz argued that demands by United States presidents for specific actions by foreign governments are common.
lead_paragraph: Closing out a long day, Alan Dershowitz, perhaps the Trump team’s best-known lawyer, said House managers had resorted to “politically loaded and promiscuously deployed” charges to cast President Trump’s conduct as impeachable.
headline_main: Dershowitz argues that nothing Bolton is said to have written would be impeachable.

abstract: As Bernie Sanders exudes confidence in his ability to win next week's Iowa caucuses, his moderate rivals are struggling with how — and whether — to directly take on the progressive Vermont senator who some Democrats worry won't be able to defeat President Donald Trump.
snippet: As Bernie Sanders exudes confidence in his ability to win next week's Iowa caucuses, his moderate rivals are struggling with how — and whether — to directly take on the progressive Vermont senator who some Democrats worry won't be able to defeat P...
lead_paragraph: CEDAR FALLS, Iowa — As Bernie Sanders exudes confidence in his ability to win next week's Iowa caucuses, his moderate rivals are struggling with how — and whether — to directly take on the progressive Vermont senator who some Democrats worry won't be able to defeat President Donald Trump.
headline_main: Democrats Struggle With How Directly to Knock Sanders
